io.netty.handler.codec.stomp

Interface StompHeaders

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ConvertibleHeaders<CharSequence,String>, Headers<CharSequence>, Iterable<Map.Entry<CharSequence,CharSequence>>, TextHeaders
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultStompHeaders

    public interface StompHeaders
extends TextHeaders
    The multimap data structure for the STOMP header names and values. It also provides the constants for the standard STOMP header names and values.

        Sets a header with the specified name and value. If there is an existing header with the same name, it is removed. If the specified value is not a String, it is converted into a String by Object.toString(), except for Date and Calendar, which are formatted to the date format defined in RFC2616.
